Two people lost their lives this morning in a car crash. The Netcare 911 spokesman, Shawn Herbst said Netcare 911 responded to reports of a collision on R82 between Roshnee and De Deur. "Reports from the scene indicate that a bakkie and a car were involved in a collision," said Herbst. "Paramedics assessed the scene and found that an adult male and adult female had sustained fatal injuries," he added. Herbst said four adult males from the bakkie sustained moderate injuries. 